Introduction: - The Centrally Sponsored Scheme for Strengthening Teaching, Learning and Outcome of Education System in the State (STARS), funded by the World Bank, is being implemented in the State from the year 2021-22. The scheme is funded by the Central Government and the State Government in the ratio of 60:40 respectively. Reference No. By order 1, the Central Government has deposited the second instalment of the current financial year 2024-25 for the general component in the Consolidated Fund of the State. The proposal for devolution of State share equivalent to this fund b is referred to Reference No. 2 has been submitted to the government. A proposal to approve it was under consideration of the government.

Government Decision: - To implement the Centrally Sponsored Scheme of Strengthening Teaching, Learning and Outcome of Education System in the State (STARS) funded by the World Bank, the Central Government has released the Central share of Rs. 26,37,78, 000 / - (Characters Rs. twenty-six crores (thirty-seven lakh seventy-eight thousand) and the corresponding State share of Rs. 197,58,52, 000 / - (Characters Rs. 2. The grant is a conditional grant and the utilization certificate of the funds disbursed earlier has been submitted. The terms and conditions of this grant are set out in the said Government Decision.

3. The Central Government while spending the said fund. The terms and conditions mentioned in the fund distribution order dated 26.03.2025 should be strictly adhered to. Care should be taken to ensure that the funds for items B will be spent within the same limits as those items for which the funds have been allocated, as shown in the table above.

Expenditure on Scheduled Castes application under the World Bank-funded Strengthening the Teaching, Learning and Outcome of Education System in the State (STARS) scheme should be made from the Single Nodal Account (SNA) account.

The State Project Director, Maharashtra Primary Education Council, Mumbai shall strictly follow the financial rules in the Maharashtra Budget Manual, Financial Authority Manual and the directions given in the Government Circular with reference to the Finance Department while spending the said provision. It should be ensured that the funds are spent in this year as per the approved plan in line with the existing government policy on expenditure.

6. The Under Secretary / Cell Officer (Cash / Accounts Branch), School Education & Sports Department, Mantralaya, Mumbai is being declared as the Drawing & Disbursing Officer and Joint / Deputy Secretary, School Education Sports Department, Mantralaya, Mumbai as the Controlling Officer for the collection and disbursement of these funds.

The concerned Drawing and Disbursing Officer should withdraw the funds from the treasury and deposit them in the concerned back account under the State Project Director, Maharashtra Council of Elementary Education.

7. Further proposals for redemption should be submitted along with information such as title-wise / sub-heading report of expenditure incurred from the provision made available, certificate of utilization of funds, etc.
